<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="535" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Walter S. Robertson</persName>, at
                                Peiping</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-12">12 June 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>877. Yeh<note n="59" xml:id="d535fn59">Gen. Yeh Chien-ying, Chinese
                                Communist Commissioner of the Executive Headquarters at
                                Peiping.</note> informs Chou that Nationalist in Operations
                            [Division] stated Tu Li-ming will resume advance, attack, pursuit on
                            10th and then withdrew from meeting. Is this a fact? Rush reply.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>